The paper discusses community detection in social networks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of social and information networks (cs.SI), social and economic systems (cs.SOC), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of node attributes, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it involves using additional information to improve the performance of algorithms. Finally, the paper provides a comprehensive survey of available results, which falls under the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE) as it involves evaluating and comparing different methods. However, since the focus of the paper is on community detection, the other sub-categories are more likely to be relevant.
